hts into the present and future of cultural production and distribution in the digital age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAnimated filmsxHistory and criticismxJapan. 0aAnimated filmszJapanxHistory and criticism. 0aComic books, strips, etcxHistory and criticismxJapan. 0aComic books, strips, etczJapanxHistory and criticism. 0aFans (Persons). 0aPopular culturexJapan. 0aPopular culturexJapanese influences. 0aPopular culturezJapan. 0aSubculturexJapan. 0aSubculturezJapan. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh1 aAzuma, Hiroki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEng, Lawrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIshida, Kimi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIto, Mizuko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIto, Mizuko, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKijima, Yoshimasa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKitada, Akihiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorikawa, Kaichiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOkabe, Daisuke, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOkabe, Daisuke, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTamagawa, Hiroaki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTsuji, Izumi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTsuji, Izumi, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030017826540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300178265423Coveruhttps://w